    {
      "id": "RQ-0072",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Prevent stale or recycled refs from silently targeting different elements",
      "description": "Add stale-ref safety for page-scoped refs so agents cannot easily reuse an old-looking `@eNN` after navigation and hit an unrelated current-page element. Dogfood found an old Wikipedia search ref number later clicked a different Tools control instead of failing as stale.",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "dogfood",
        "refs",
        "stale-ref",
        "correctness"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "extensions/agent-browser/index.ts",
        "extensions/agent-browser/lib/results/shared.ts",
        "extensions/agent-browser/lib/results/presentation.ts",
        "docs/TOOL_CONTRACT.md",
        "docs/COMMAND_REFERENCE.md",
        "test/agent-browser.extension-validation.test.ts",
        "test/agent-browser.results.test.ts"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "dogfood 2026-05-14 interactive pass :: after navigating from Wikipedia home/search, reusing `@e34` clicked the current page's `button \"Tools\"` rather than producing a stale-ref warning for the prior Search button.",
        "dogfood 2026-05-14 static/docs pass :: stale-ref handling was helpful when it did trigger, but retry guidance lacked named-session context."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Investigate whether upstream exposes enough snapshot/page identity to associate refs with a generation token.",
        "If feasible, preserve snapshot generation metadata in tool output and detect/refuse stale generation mismatches for mutation-prone actions.",
        "If upstream cannot support generation checks, add best-effort warnings that include current element name/role and prior snapshot context when known.",
        "Update stale-ref nextActions to request a fresh session-aware snapshot before retrying.",
        "Add regression coverage for ref reuse after navigation and for safe current-page ref usage."
      ],
      "notes": [],
      "request": "dogfood feedback from two pi agents on native agent_browser tool, 2026-05-14",
      "created_at": "2026-05-14T20:19:11Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-05-14T20:19:11Z",
      "depends_on": [
        "RQ-0071"
      ],
      "blocks": [],
      "relates_to": [],
      "custom_fields": {
        "dogfood_order": "4"
      }
