    {
      "id": "RQ-0073",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Surface likely overlay blockers when clicks do not change page state",
      "description": "Improve click-result diagnostics when an action reports success but no URL or meaningful DOM state changes occur because a fixed overlay, modal, banner, or dialog may be intercepting the intended workflow. Dogfood on Wikipedia needed a screenshot to discover a donation banner close button before search would navigate.",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "dogfood",
        "clicks",
        "diagnostics",
        "overlays"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "extensions/agent-browser/lib/results/presentation.ts",
        "extensions/agent-browser/lib/results/shared.ts",
        "extensions/agent-browser/index.ts",
        "docs/TOOL_CONTRACT.md",
        "docs/COMMAND_REFERENCE.md",
        "test/agent-browser.presentation.test.ts",
        "test/agent-browser.extension-validation.test.ts"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "dogfood 2026-05-14 interactive pass :: clicking Wikipedia Search reported success but stayed on the same URL; a screenshot later revealed a Wikimedia donation banner/overlay with close button `@e5` blocking progress."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Inspect available post-click page-change summary and snapshot evidence for detecting no-op clicks and overlays.",
        "When a mutation-prone click has no URL/state change, surface likely blockers such as visible fixed overlays, dialogs, banners, and close buttons if evidence is available.",
        "Add a conservative nextAction for re-snapshot or close-overlay only when safe; avoid inventing blockers without evidence.",
        "Document the diagnostic limits and add tests with a fixture overlay."
      ],
      "notes": [],
      "request": "dogfood feedback from two pi agents on native agent_browser tool, 2026-05-14",
