      "id": "RQ-0074",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Prefer or warn about visible elements for selector text reads",
      "description": "Make `get text <selector>` less misleading on tabbed/hidden DOM content. Dogfood found `get text .language-bash` returned npm command text after the visible Playwright tab had switched to yarn, likely because the first matching hidden code block was read.",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "dogfood",
        "get-text",
        "selectors",
        "visibility"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "extensions/agent-browser/lib/results/presentation.ts",
        "extensions/agent-browser/index.ts",
        "docs/COMMAND_REFERENCE.md",
        "docs/TOOL_CONTRACT.md",
        "test/agent-browser.presentation.test.ts",
        "test/agent-browser.extension-validation.test.ts"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "dogfood 2026-05-14 static/docs pass :: after clicking Playwright `yarn` tab, DOM eval showed active tab text `yarn`, but `get text .language-bash` returned `npm init playwright@latest` from a first/hidden match."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Determine whether upstream supports visible-only selector reads or exposes match counts/visibility metadata for `get text`.",
        "Prefer visible matches by default when safe, or add a warning when selector results may include hidden/multiple elements.",
        "Document selector best practices for tabbed pages and visible-only alternatives if upstream provides them.",
        "Add tests for hidden-first selector content and ensure existing text reads remain stable."
      ],
