    {
      "id": "RQ-0075",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Classify benign network failures in QA and diagnostics",
      "description": "Reduce QA false negatives and raw diagnostic noise by classifying failed network requests by likely impact. Dogfood saw `qa` fail on `example.com` solely because `/favicon.ico` returned 404 even though expected text, page load, console, errors, and screenshot were fine.",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "dogfood",
        "qa",
        "network",
        "diagnostics"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "extensions/agent-browser/index.ts",
        "extensions/agent-browser/lib/results/presentation.ts",
        "extensions/agent-browser/lib/results/shared.ts",
        "docs/TOOL_CONTRACT.md",
        "docs/COMMAND_REFERENCE.md",
        "README.md",
        "test/agent-browser.extension-validation.test.ts",
        "test/agent-browser.presentation.test.ts"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "dogfood 2026-05-14 interactive pass :: `qa` on `https://example.com` found expected text, no console/page errors, and saved screenshot but failed because `https://example.com/favicon.ico` returned 404.",
        "dogfood 2026-05-14 interactive pass :: `network requests` and `networkSourceLookup` were useful but too raw for QA triage, repeatedly surfacing favicon noise."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Audit `qa` failure classification and network presentation paths.",
        "Classify common low-impact asset failures such as `favicon.ico` separately from document/API/script failures.",
        "Decide whether benign failures should warn instead of failing by default, while preserving strict opt-in behavior for users who want it.",
        "Add compact network diagnostic summaries grouped by status/resource type and common-noise classification.",
        "Update docs/tests for QA pass/warn/fail semantics."
      ],
      "notes": [],
