      "id": "RQ-0076",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Return partial progress and artifact evidence when jobs time out",
      "description": "Make long `job`/`batch` workflows recoverable when the wrapper watchdog fires. Dogfood found a realistic DuckDuckGo job exceeded the 28s wrapper watchdog and returned an actionable timeout message but no last completed step, active step, current URL/title, or artifact paths already created.",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "dogfood",
        "job",
        "batch",
        "timeouts",
        "artifacts"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "extensions/agent-browser/index.ts",
        "extensions/agent-browser/lib/process.ts",
        "extensions/agent-browser/lib/results/presentation.ts",
        "extensions/agent-browser/lib/results/shared.ts",
        "docs/TOOL_CONTRACT.md",
        "docs/COMMAND_REFERENCE.md",
        "test/agent-browser.extension-validation.test.ts",
        "test/agent-browser.presentation.test.ts"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "dogfood 2026-05-14 interactive pass :: DuckDuckGo job with open/wait/fill/screenshot/click/wait/assert/screenshot exceeded wrapper watchdog; output did not include partial step evidence or artifact paths.",
        "dogfood 2026-05-14 interactive pass :: agent had to manually inspect whether `ddg-job-filled.png` existed after timeout."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Inspect process timeout handling, upstream batch output shape, and artifact manifest collection on failed invocations.",
        "Return best-effort partial progress: last completed step, active/failed step when known, current URL/title if safely available, and verified artifacts created before timeout.",
        "Consider an explicit timeout/budget parameter for top-level `job` or clearer guidance to split long waits.",
        "Ensure timeout evidence is redacted and bounded.",
        "Add fake-upstream timeout regressions for partial artifacts and batch-step context."
      ],
      "notes": [],
