      "id": "RQ-0077",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Report managed-session outcome after failed fresh launches or jobs",
      "description": "Make post-failure recovery clearer by stating whether a failed `sessionMode: fresh` call replaced, preserved, or abandoned the managed session. Dogfood saw a timed-out fresh DuckDuckGo job followed by plain `snapshot -i` showing the previous Wikipedia/Wikisource page, and the timeout output did not explain whether the previous auto session was preserved.",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "dogfood",
        "sessions",
        "timeouts",
        "recovery"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "extensions/agent-browser/index.ts",
        "extensions/agent-browser/lib/runtime.ts",
        "extensions/agent-browser/lib/results/shared.ts",
        "docs/TOOL_CONTRACT.md",
        "docs/COMMAND_REFERENCE.md",
        "test/agent-browser.extension-validation.test.ts",
        "test/agent-browser.runtime.test.ts"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "dogfood 2026-05-14 interactive pass :: after timed-out DuckDuckGo `job` with `sessionMode: fresh`, plain `snapshot -i` still showed the previous session page; output did not state whether the fresh session was abandoned or current auto session preserved."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Trace managed-session state transitions for failed fresh launches, timeouts, and compiled job/qa flows.",
        "Add a concise `managedSessionOutcome` or equivalent detail on failure paths that states preserved/replaced/unknown with session/page context when safe.",
        "Ensure recovery nextActions reflect the actual current managed session state.",
        "Add tests for fresh failure preserving prior session and fresh success replacing it."
      ],
      "notes": [],
